"{\"uid\": \"nbcsports.com-pressbox-press-releases-nbcuniversal-to-provide-its-most-comprehensive-audio-coverage-ever-for-olympic-games-paris-2024\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"NBCUniversal's Audio Coverage for Paris Olympics Includes iHeartMedia Play-by-Play Channels, Original Podcasts, and More  STAMFORD, Conn. - July 25, 2024- With the Opening Ceremony of the Olympic Games Paris 2024 beginning tomorrow, NBCUniversal is providing audio coverage that features expansive ways for fans to listen to their favorite events, competitions, and athletes than ever before, providing all new play-by-play channels, original podcasts, and more.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 462, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 0, \"end\": 12, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBCUniversal\", \"score\": 0.9999993363987797, \"rank\": 6.612285857021139e-07, \"text\": \"NBCUniversal\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBCUniversal\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBCUniversal\"}, {\"begin\": 122, \"end\": 130, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stamford_Transportation_Center\", \"score\": 0.9999977945346237, \"rank\": 2.2054398724511004e-06, \"text\": \"STAMFORD\", \"types\": [\"Q719456\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stamford_Transportation_Center\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stamford_Transportation_Center\"}, {\"begin\": 233, \"end\": 245, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBCUniversal\", \"score\": 0.9999993363987797, \"rank\": 6.612285857021139e-07, \"text\": \"NBCUniversal\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBCUniversal\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBCUniversal\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Following are all the ways for U.S. fans to listen to the Paris Olympics:  iHeartMedia: NBCUniversal has chosen iHeartMedia as its exclusive audio partner for the Olympic Games Paris 2024.\", \"from\": 464, \"to\": 652, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 552, \"end\": 564, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBCUniversal\", \"score\": 0.9999993363987797, \"rank\": 6.612285857021139e-07, \"text\": \"NBCUniversal\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBCUniversal\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBCUniversal\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"As part of the agreement, iHeartRadio is launching 24/7 play-by-play audio channels of select NBCU linear coverage of the Games; has created an original Olympic iHeartPodcast hosted byBowen YangandMatt Rogers; will produce Olympic-specific episodes from some of iHeart's top podcasts; and is promoting tune-in for NBCU's comprehensive coverage.\", \"from\": 653, \"to\": 997, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 747, \"end\": 751, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBCUniversal\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"NBCU\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBCUniversal\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBCUniversal\"}, {\"begin\": 967, \"end\": 971, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBCUniversal\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"NBCU\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBCUniversal\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBCUniversal\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Podium:The Podiumreturns for its fourth season, with weekly episodes leading up to Paris and then daily in-Games.\", \"from\": 999, \"to\": 1116, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1086, \"end\": 1091, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999989051958, \"rank\": 1.094758148364203e-09, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Join NBC Sports hostZora Stephensonon a deep dive into the heart of the Paris Olympics with insider coverage, athlete features and the most memorable storylines, for one of the most anticipated Games in recent memory.\", \"from\": 1117, \"to\": 1334, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1122, \"end\": 1132, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_Sports\", \"score\": 0.9999743102160444, \"rank\": 2.5464111992559058e-05, \"text\": \"NBC Sports\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_Sports\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_Sports\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This season includes four weekly bonus episodes with behind-the-scenes interviews from the U.S. Olympic and Paralympic athlete summit.\", \"from\": 1335, \"to\": 1469, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1443, \"end\": 1461, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paralympic_sports\", \"score\": 0.9994244094118674, \"rank\": 0.0005759220835506689, \"text\": \"Paralympic athlete\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paralympic_sports\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paralympic_sports\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In The Village:TheIn The Villagepodcast returns daily during the Games, where Olympic medalistElizabeth Beiseltakes listeners into one of the most exclusive areas of the Paris Olympics - the athletes' village -- to explore the daily life of athletes as they arrive, train and perform in this unprecedented environment.\", \"from\": 1471, \"to\": 1789, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"My New Favorite Olympian:NBCUniversal Local's NBC-owned stations and NBC Sports Regional Networks present a new season of the award-winning multiplatform podcastMy New Favorite Olympianprofiling Team USA's most-inspiring athletes leading up to Paris 2024.\", \"from\": 1791, \"to\": 2046, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1816, \"end\": 1828, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBCUniversal\", \"score\": 0.9999993363987797, \"rank\": 6.612285857021139e-07, \"text\": \"NBCUniversal\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBCUniversal\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBCUniversal\"}, {\"begin\": 1860, \"end\": 1888, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_Sports_Regional_Networks\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.533093515249334e-25, \"text\": \"NBC Sports Regional Networks\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_Sports_Regional_Networks\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_Sports_Regional_Networks\"}, {\"begin\": 1955, \"end\": 1967, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Favorite\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"New Favorite\", \"types\": [\"Q482994\", \"Q386724\", \"Q2188189\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Favorite\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Favorite\"}, {\"begin\": 1986, \"end\": 1994, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9635232643744486, \"rank\": 0.0334292618619795, \"text\": \"Team USA\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 2035, \"end\": 2045, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.1090269345792966e-27, \"text\": \"Paris 2024\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The seven-part audio and video series, which began June 12, is led by 12-time Olympic medalist swimmerNatalie CoughlinandZena Keita, an NBC Sports Bay Area reporter, host and analyst.\", \"from\": 2047, \"to\": 2230, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2183, \"end\": 2202, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_Sports_Bay_Area\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"NBC Sports Bay Area\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_Sports_Bay_Area\", \"dbpedia\": \"http:/